            Modular building blocks\\[1pt]
            3 tasks $\times$ 3 creativity\\
            $\times$ 3 lengths = 1{,}389 prompts
        };
        \node[phase, fill=gray!12, right=1.1cm of p1] (p2) {%
            \textbf{\small Phase 2}\\[3pt]
            \textbf{\small LLM Generation}\\[5pt]
            \scriptsize 10 models $\times$ 5 temps\\[1pt]
            53 runs\\[1pt]
            $N{=}12{,}469$ outputs\\[1pt]
        };
        \node[phase, fill=blue!7, right=1.1cm of p2] (p3) {%
            \textbf{\small Phase 3}\\[3pt]
            \textbf{\small HalluLens Verification}\\[5pt]
            \scriptsize (i) Abstention filter\\[1pt]
            (ii) Claim extraction (LLM)\\[1pt]
            (iii) Dense retrieval (Wiki)\\[1pt]
            (iv) NLI verdict: \texttt{S}/\texttt{H}
        };
        \node[phase, fill=gray!12, right=1.1cm of p3] (p4) {%
            \textbf{\small Phase 4}\\[3pt]
            \textbf{\small Statistical Analysis}\\[5pt]
            \scriptsize generalized linear model (odds ratios)\\[1pt]
            generalized linear mixed model (prompt variance)\\[1pt]
            Mediation analysis\\[1pt]
        };

        \draw[arrow] (p1.east) -- (p2.west);
        \draw[arrow] (p2.east) -- (p3.west);
        \draw[arrow] (p3.east) -- (p4.west);
    \end{tikzpicture}}%
    \caption{Four-phase experimental pipeline.
    Phases~1--2 construct and generate 12{,}469 outputs from 10 models by
    factorial crossing of task, creativity level, and length.
    Phase~3 applies the HalluLens verification paradigm \citep{bang_hallulens_2025}:
    atomic claim extraction, dense Wikipedia retrieval (\texttt{gtr-t5-large}),
    and NLI verdict (\texttt{S}upported / \texttt{H}allucinated).
    Phase~4 analyses effects via GLM, GLMM, and mediation with false discovery rate (FDR) correction
    \citep{benjamini_controlling_1995}.
    Full protocol in Appendix~\ref{app:details}.}
    \label{fig:pipeline}
\end{figure*}


\subsection{Pipeline Overview}

Figure~\ref{fig:pipeline} summarizes the pipeline.
We cross three task types, three creativity levels, and three target lengths over Wikipedia subjects to assemble 1{,}389 prompts, none granting permission to invent facts ($\kappa$ low throughout) and generate 12{,}469 outputs from 10 models (Phases~1--2).
Claims are extracted with \textbf{mimo-v2-flash}~\cite{xiaomi2026mimov2flash}, verified against Wikipedia via dense retrieval and NLI following HalluLens \citep{bang_hallulens_2025} (Phase~3; 310K claims, 60\% hallucinated on average), and analyzed (Phase~4; details in Appendix~\ref{app:details}).

\subsection{Empirical Findings}\label{sec:results}
% === CLAIMS SUPPORTED HERE ===
% C1: CI proxy (creativity_level/rank) associates with hallucination_rate under tasks/controls.
% C2: heterogeneity across tasks/models; confounding risk acknowledged.

Table~\ref{tab:key-findings} consolidates the main effects and the task$\times$creativity interaction. We highlight three qualitative phenomena that motivate \TR-aware evaluation:

